<H3> <TI>   Ukraine Strikes Barter Arrangement With Russia for Cost of 
Natural Gas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  944K0522B Moscow SELSKAYA ZHIZN in Russian 31 Dec 93 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 944K0522B </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SELSKAYA ZHIZN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Toward Repayment of the Debt"] </F>
  [Text] Nikolayev--Four large refrigerating trawlers will be 
turned over to fishermen of the Far East toward repayment of a 
proportion of the debt of Ukraine for natural gas to the Gazprom 
concern of the Russian Federation. The crews of these vessels 
are scheduled to arrive in Nikolayev shortly. The 
Ukrnefteprodukt association will refund the cost of the vessels 
in karbovantsy to the shipyard. This impressive barter operation 
between the two CIS states became possible as a result of 
negotiations initiated in Moscow and Kiev by specialists from 
the Black Sea Shipbuilding Plant. During the negotiations, 
opportunities for the delivery of a total of 15 trawlers with 
similar arrangements for mutual settlements was discussed. 

</TEXT>

