  [Abstract] This article examines discrete orthogonal 
transforms in Galua fields implemented without multiplications. 
Algorithms in which multiplication is replaced by register 
shifts are found to be more efficient. Discrete orthogonal 
transforms are examined in finite fields with representation of 
the input in nontraditional notation systems (e.g., systems with 
