Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by G. P. Kovtun, A. I. Kravchenko, A. I. Zhukov, A. </F>
N. Sterlev, A. P Shcherban] 
  [Abstract]Computer modelling is used to compute temperature 
fields in GaAs monocrystals grown in a thin layer of melt by the 
Kiropolous method with liquid sealing. The results of the 
calculations are given. It is shown that by using a bottom 
heater, a side heater and an additional heater sunk in flux, the 
