<H3> <TI>   Pneumatic Disinsection of Vegetable Plantings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  947C0045A Moscow ZASHCHITA RASTENIY in Russian No 2, Feb 93 
p 24 </F>

<F P=103> 947C0045A </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ZASHCHITA RASTENIY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by V.P. Marmalyukov, M.I. Astakhov, V.P. Polobok, </F>
I.T. Korol, L.I. Prishchepa, N.I. Mikulskaya; UDC 635.1/8:631.34] 
  [Abstract] A 2.8-m-wide experimental pneumatic vegetable 
planting disinsection unit for class 1.4 tractors developed by 
the Scientific Production Association of Belarussian 
Agricultural Mechanization is described. The pneumatic vegetable 
planting disinsection unit consists of a vacuum chamber which 
carries an axial-flow controlled output fan and guides for 
changing the flow direction as well as insect intake chambers. 
The operating procedure is outlined in detail. A pilot prototype 
of the PDO-4.2 disinsectization unit has been developed on the 
basis of this device and has passed preliminary tests at the 
Belarussian Machine Testing Station. The device manufactured by 
the pilot plant of the Central Scientific Research Institute of 
Rural Mechanization and Electrification in Agriculture has been 
integrated in the vegetable agriculture mechanization system of 
the Belarus Republic. Figures 1. 


</TEXT>

